Additional relevant crops: okra, cabbage, cauliflower, peppers, tomato, potato, maize and cotton<br/>-&nbsp;Check fields for cutworms before sowing or transplanting. Monitor damage by counting damaged and freshly cut leaves, freshly cut young plants, and holes in leaves and in stems
<br/>-&nbsp;Check on plants daily for green to dark-brown caterpillars at base of plant and underside of leaves, observe for whitening or chlorotic lesions on fresh leaves and dried leaves<br/>-&nbsp;Early in the morning flush larvae using a mixture of lemon scenting  dish washing liquid at 2 tablespoons/2 gal of water <br/>-&nbsp;If 5-10 caterpillars per 10 plants are observed, initiate control measures<br/>

-&nbsp;If the disease is severe, copper fungicides can be applied.&nbsp;General Restrictions:&nbsp;Apply using a 15L pneumatic knapsack sprayer at 4 week intervals during the rainy season when there are pods to protect.
